longBusinessSummary: Amplia Therapeutics Limited, a pharmaceutical company, focuses on advancing a pipeline of focal adhesion kinase (FAK) inhibitors for cancer and fibrosis in Australia. The company's clinical development pipeline comprises two lead molecules, AMP945 and AMP886 that inhibits (FAK). It has a collaboration agreement with the Garvan Institute of Media Research in Sydney. The company was formerly known as Innate Immunotherapeutics Limited and changed its name to Amplia Therapeutics Limited in September 2018. Amplia Therapeutics Limited was incorporated in 2000 and is based in Melbourne, Australia.
